# Project Documentation: Health Insurance Management System (HIMS)

## 1. Project Overview
The **Health Insurance Management System (HIMS)** is a comprehensive web application designed to streamline the insurance lifecycle. It facilitates everything from quote generation and policy management to claim processing and agent commission tracking. The system supports multiple user roles, each with a tailored dashboard and specific permissions.

### Key Objectives
- **Accessibility**: Provide customers with instant premium quotes.
- **Efficiency**: Automate policy creation and claim workflows.
- **Transparency**: Track agent performance and commissions in real-time.
- **Security**: Manage sensitive documents through a secure Document Vault.

---

## 2. Technology Stack

### Backend
- **Framework**: ASP.NET Core Web API (.NET 8.0)
- **Database**: SQL Server
- **ORM**: Entity Framework Core (Code-First Approach)
- **Authentication**: JWT (JSON Web Tokens) with Role-based access control.
- **Architecture**: Clean Architecture (Domain, Application, Infrastructure, API).

### Frontend
- **Framework**: Angular 17+
- **Styling**: Vanilla CSS / Angular Material
- **API Integration**: RxJS-based services for seamless backend communication.

---

## 3. Domain Entities (Database Schema)

Every entity in the system inherits from a **BaseEntity**, which includes common audit fields:
- `Id` (int): Primary Key.
- `CreatedAt` (DateTime): Timestamp of creation.
- `UpdatedAt` (DateTime?): Timestamp of last modification.
- `IsActive` (bool): Soft-delete flag.

### 3.1 User
Managed in the [User](file:///c:/Users/Koushik%20Gaddam/OneDrive/Desktop/KOUSHIK/backend/HealthInsurance.Domain/Entities/User.cs#10-17) class, representing all stakeholders in the system.
| Variable | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `FullName` | string | The full name of the user. |
| `Email` | string | Unique email used for login. |
| `PasswordHash` | string | Encrypted password storage. |
| `Role` | UserRole | Enum: Admin, Agent, Customer, ClaimsOfficer. |

### 3.2 Policy
Represents a specific insurance plan held by a customer or a template for plans.
| Variable | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `PolicyNumber` | string | Unique identifier for the policy. |
| `UserId` | int | ID of the customer owning the policy. |
| `PlanName` | string | Name of the insurance plan (e.g., "Family Health"). |
| `MonthlyPremium`| decimal | Cost per month for the policy. |
| `CoverageAmount`| decimal | Maximum claimable amount. |
| `ExpiryDate` | DateTime | When the policy coverage ends. |
| `Status` | string | Current state (Active, Lapsed, Cancelled). |
| `AgentId` | int? | The agent assigned to manage this policy. |
| `IsPlanTemplate` | bool | True if this is a master plan template used by Admins. |

### 3.3 PremiumQuote
Generated when a user (or guest) requests a quote.
| Variable | Type | Description |
